urlLink KnoxNews: Columnists : "Will Head  Start stay in the race?  By INA HUGHS, hugh@knews.com August 26, 2003  In a speech before the American people on April 3, 2002, President Bush looked us in the face and said: 'Our goal as a nation must be to make sure that no child is denied the chance to grow in knowledge and character from their very first years.' He said that. In plain English.    So what language is he speaking and how can he justify the about-face when now, a year later, he wants to dismantle Head Start, the premier early childhood program for disadvantaged preschoolers?   "